@apoelstra: The last sentence of the Abstract of the [currently published version](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0093.mediawiki#abstract) of BIP93 reads:

> A minimum threshold of shares, which can be between 1 and 9, is needed to recover the secret, whereas without sufficient shares, no information about the secret is recoverable.

@Lil-Duckling-22: Please incorporate the requested changes.

@apoelstra @BenWestgate 
Made changes
So many comments and thoughts, hope I did it right
